tney-Wonder-Jagger-John-Gaga@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/McCartney-Wonder-Jagger-John-Gaga@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/McCartney-Wonder-Jagger-John-Gaga@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/McCartney-Wonder-Jagger-John-Gaga@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/McCartney-Wonder-Jagger-John-Gaga@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/McCartney-Wonder-Jagger-John-Gaga@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-rolling-stones">滚石乐队</a>分享了他们即将发行的专辑“Hackney Diamonds”的完整曲目列表，并确认<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/paul-mccartney">保罗·麦卡特尼</a>、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/lady-gaga">Lady Gaga</a> 、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/elton-john">埃尔顿·约翰</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/stevie-wonder">史蒂维·旺德</a>将在这张专辑中亮相。</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/the-rolling-stones-new-album-release-date-hackney-diamonds-3494545">The Rolling Stones&#39; return is an even bigger bang</a><br /></strong></li></ul><p> The classic rock icons <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-confirm-new-album-hackney-diamonds-and-single-angry-3494112">announced details of their forthcoming 24th studio record last week</a> and shared its lead single &#39;Angry&#39;, which came with a music video starring <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/euphoria"><em>Euphoria</em></a> star Sydney Sweeney.</p><p> The new LP was announced at a globally live-streamed event from Hackney Empire in East London last Wednesday (September 6), hosted by <em>The Tonight Show</em> host Jimmy Fallon. Here, <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/keith-richards">Keith Richards</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/mick-jagger">Mick Jagger</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/ronnie-wood">Ronnie Wood</a> shared details on the upcoming release, and confirmed it will be their first new music in 18 years – following on from 2005&#39;s <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/reviews-the-rolling-stones-7763-312997#:~:text=This%20is%20an%20old%2Dfashioned,well%20be%20by%20Sheryl%20Crow.">&#39;A Bigger Bang&#39;</a> .</p><p> Now, the members have shared the full tracklist of the 12-song album, and confirmed that it will feature an array of guest stars, as well as <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-reveal-charlie-watts-appears-on-two-tracks-of-new-album-hackney-diamonds-3494170">tracks recorded with late drummer Charlie Watts.</a></p><p> Watts features on two of the songs in the listing – &#39;Mess It Up&#39; and &#39;Live By The Sword&#39;. These appear back-to-back, midway through the album and the latter also features bass from former Stones bassist Bill Wyman. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="The launch of #HackneyDiamonds was a little bigger than NME having a pint with @mickjagger" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/qq_ZTdjh-qg?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Sir Elton John also performs on the latter track, playing piano for the song. He features on another track too, adding keys to &#39;Get Close&#39; – the second song on the tracklist.</p><p> Lady Gaga contributes vocals to the penultimate song, titled &#39;Sweet Sounds Of Heaven&#39;, and music icon Stevie Wonder also stars on the track, playing keys and piano.</p><p> Finally, former Beatle legend Paul McCartney joins forces with Mick Jagger and co. for the forthcoming album, and plays the bass in a song called &#39;Bite My Head Off&#39;. Check out the full tracklist below. </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/Cw2rEeYsWYV/?u